fields.value: U.S. National Survey of Young Women, 1979

datasetContactAffiliation.value: University of California, Los Angeles. Social Science Data Archive.

dsDescriptionValue.value: Like the 1971 and 1976 National Surveys of Young Women, the major purpose of this study was to provide estimates of the prevalence of sexual activity, contraceptive use and non-use, premarital pregnancy and its resolution among teenage women. This study also attempted to determine how informed young men were about contraception and the menstrual cycle. This dataset is a subset of the full study, and was put together by Sociometrics Corp.
